The paper focuses on the interaction between the driver and the driving automation system, specifically on the driver's trust in the system and how it affects their behavior. This falls under the category of human-computer interaction (cs.HC). Additionally, the paper uses a driving simulator and a driver monitoring system, which involves robotics (cs.RO) and artificial intelligence (cs.AI). The paper also discusses the potential risks of over-trusting the automation system, which relates to cybersecurity (cs.CYBER) and system safety (cs.SY).
